            type="application/octet-stream"/>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[
                <h2>✨ Version 1.1.3 - Setup Improvements & Fixes</h2>
                <p>Fixing issues related to sudoers permissions.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>📝 Improved:</strong> Provides clearer and more specific setup instructions if <code>sudoers</code> permissions are missing or invalid.</li>
                    <li><strong>⚙️ Change & Note:</strong> Updated the recommended <code>sudoers</code> rule in the setup instructions to <code>ALL ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: [SCRIPT_PATH]</code> for better reliability across different environments.
                        <br/><em>(Note: This manual <code>sudoers</code> configuration method is used because the standard macOS approach for privileged operations requires code signing and notarization, which necessitates a paid Apple Developer account. As a student developer, this isn't currently feasible. This alternative allows the core functionality to be used without that requirement. Thank you for your understanding.)</em>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>🐛 Fixed:</strong> Improved error handling and logging when executing the helper script, especially for <code>sudo</code> failures.</li>
                    <li><strong>🌍 Localization:</strong> Updated and added localizations for new UI text and instructions (Chinese, Japanese, French, etc.).</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Updating is recommended for all users. If you upgrade from an older version and encounter issues, you may need to update your <code>sudoers</code> file according to the new in-app instructions.</p>
                ]]>
            </description>
        </item>
